    <string name="api_key_security_explanation"><![CDATA[
        <p><b>Your API Key is stored securely</b><br>
        Your OpenAI API key is encrypted and stored securely on your device using Android\'s EncryptedSharedPreferences. This encryption uses the Android KeyStore system for maximum security.</p>
        
        <p><b>Client-side only architecture</b><br>
        All API requests are made <b>directly from your device to OpenAI</b>. Your API key is never sent to our servers or stored elsewhere.</p>
        
        <p><b>Complete transparency</b><br>
        You can view exactly how your API key is handled in our <a href="https://github.com/Tomer-Barak/PostMuse">open-source code</a>. The app code shows that API requests go directly to OpenAI\'s servers with your key.</p>
        
        <p><b>API key usage</b><br>
        Your key is only used for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Text generation with OpenAI\'s API</li>
            <li>Image analysis with Vision API</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><b>Your data stays private</b><br>
        Since we don\'t route your API requests through our servers, we never see your data or API key.</p>
    ]]></string>
    
